<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-02-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-02-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="712" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d712">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Count <persName type="from">Cassini</persName> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-02-15"><hi rend="italic">February 15,
                                    1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>: By order of my
                            Government, I have the honor to advise your excellency that, in
                            consequence of the laying of torpedoes in the waters of the Kwantung,
                            all vessels which desire to approach the coast or enter Port Arthur
                            shall observe the following rules: After heading for the entrance of the
                            port on a strictly northern course, all vessels shall stop at a distance
                            of at least 5 miles, hoist their national flag and call by signal for a
                            pilot, who will be at once sent to them to steer them to their assigned
                            berth.</p>
                        <p>Be pleased, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Count Cassini.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>